                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="color: rgb(255,255,255);"><b><span style="font-size: 20px;">Estate Liquidation Scappoose, OR<br>Auction 9am-5pm on Fri June 12 &amp; Sat June 13</span></b><br><br>Sale address is <span style="color: rgb(255,255,204);">29142 Dutch Canyon Rd. Scappoose, Oregon&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><a href="../html/gallery.php">CLICK HERE TO VIEW PHOTOS</a><br><br>
<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2784.1024012661332!2d-122.966755!3d45.749092999999995!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x5494ff60f0f136f7%3A0x5dc2e38ff2039dc2!2s29142+Dutch+Canyon+Rd%2C+Scappoose%2C+OR+97056!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sus!4v1433993939575" width="600" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0"></iframe><br><br><i>Most of you visiting our web site normally are looking for our up coming auctions but in this case due to its location we have decided to handle this sale as an Estate Liquidation with <u>auction pricing</u>! The owner had intended to open a store to sell new and used merchandise in a overstock type of setting. Well he collected a large inventory and then due to health reasons was not able to move forward. So for those of you that come to our auctions to obtain items for resale this is the sale for you. A short list of the items we have, and we have a lot, is. I am not posting the exact address until just before the sale so check the site on the morning of for the address I am doing this for security reasons. It is just a short beautiful drive, out of Scappoose but worth the drive.</i><br><br><b>Hand tools large and small</b> - Craftsman, Stanley, Ridgid and others hundreds of sockets, ratchets, end wrenches,&nbsp; visegrips, crescent wrenches, screwdrivers, pipe wrenches (up to 36&quot;) and much much more<br><br><b>Power Tools</b> - Craftsman, Makita, Skill, and others - Drills, Jig saws, Circular Saws, Recip saws, Cordless tools, Rotozip&#39;s , Battery Chargers, Electric Impact, Shop vac&#39;s and much more.<br><br><b>Air Tools</b> - Drills, impacts, grinders, hoses, and more.<br><br><b>Hardware</b> - Nuts and bolts, nails, screws, all manner of home hardware, chain hooks and clevises, pins, storage bins, Nut and bolt bins, Almost 100 light fixtures still new in box for indoor and out door lights, Shop lights, Electrical Hardware, Ceiling Fans, Garage Door Openers and more much of this is still new in box.<br><br><b>Tool Chests and boxes</b> - Craftsman, Kennedy, bottom rolling boxes, hand carry tool boxes and other<br><br><b>Hydraulic Jacks</b> - Many sizes large and small<br><br><b>Chain Saw&#39;s &amp; Supplies</b> - New in box Polian Chain Saws, Electric Chain Saws, chainsaw parts (bars, chain, ect) Husky, Oregon, McCullagh, Makita, Homelite, and others (all new in box) <br><br><b>Shop Equipment</b> - Table Saws, Drill Presses, Band Saw, Compressor, Tire balancer, Grinder on Pedestal, Battery Chargers, Cutting torch on cart with bottles, Jack Stands, <br><br><b>Out Door Equipment</b> - Shovels, Rakes, Axes, Wedges, and other Most new some used, 2500 PSI Power Washer, Walk behind rototiller, Sprayers 15 gallon, Wheel borrows,&nbsp; cement tools, gas water pumps, 3000 watt Generator (new) and more<br><br><b>Rolling Stock </b>-&nbsp; John Deere Tractor 4300 4 wheel drive hydrostatic transmission 3pt runs great, John Deere 48&quot; Lawn Tractor, Tandem axle trailer, 48&quot; Brush Mower, 3pt rear blade, small yard trailers, and more.<br><br><b>Lumber and Roofing</b> - Plywood, Plywood rack for in shop, 4x4 pres treated, large timbers, peg board, 12&#39;x24&quot; corrugated roofing, 8&#39; Cyclone fencing, and more.<br><br><b>Household items</b> (some of this is new) - Chairs, tables, desks, New Brass lamps stands, Glass, Brass decorations, Stereo cabinets, locking cabinets, metal file cabinets, Large Brass Ships Bell, Nautical theme brass clocks - barometers and other brass items, Antique sewing machine, very nice brass mens butler and more.<br><br><span style="color: rgb(255,255,0);">If you have questions please call me at 503-720-5580 before 8:30am or after 3pm as there is no cell service at this location.</span> Saturday all items under $50 will be half price so come on Friday to get the good stuff and Saturday to get some really good deals. Most items will be $1 unless otherwise marked !!!!!! We need to get it all out of there so the owner can clean up the place! Follow the signs and we will have the address up the day before the sale!! See you there!!!!<br><br><a href="../html/gallery.php">CLICK HERE TO VIEW PHOTOS</a><br><br>We accept Visa, Mastercard, American Express.</span></p>
